LARAVEL DOCUMENTATION
- download composer from google
- open cmd and type "composer"
- go to https://laravel.com/docs/9.x/installation to install the laravel (php)
- you should have node.js, php and npm installed on the laptop as the requirements
- open cmd
- the recommendation is to use the xampp -> htdocs -> project filename
- but what I did is I create folder outside xampp
- in the cmd type "composer create-project laravel/laravel example-app(filename) 8.0 (laravel version)"
- or other way to have laravel project - composer global require laravel/installer
 				       - laravel new cd example-app 
- cd (filename)
- to download auth -"composer require laravel/ui"
- type: "php artisan ui bootstrap (since we will use bootstrap) "
- type: npm install 
- type: npm run dev (so that the dependencies will be compiled)a
- yes (Do you want to install 'webpack-cli' (yes/no): no)



// other way
cmd

- to download auth -"composer require laravel/ui"
- php artisan ui bootstrap --auth
- php artisan 


DATABASE

Player/Coach

User_id 
Photo
First name
Last name
Middle initial
Nickname/Alias
Sex
Address
Province
City
Country
Nationality
Birth date
Email
Contact no.
Tel no.
Role
Facebook
Instagram
Twitter
Username
Password


Clubs

Club_id
Club name
Club_logo
President
City
User_id (FK) (as members)
Status - via admin


